block append SpecificContent

  article

    +CallableExpressionScheme--YDF_DK({
      technicalName: "buildPhoneNumberLinkHrefAttributeValue",
      headingTag: "h1",
      parametersSpecification: [
        {
          genericTechnicalName: "phoneNumber",
          type: "string",
          required: true
        }
      ],
      returnedValue: "string"
    })

    p.Article-Paragraph.
      Generates such value of the #[+Term--YDID HTML attribute] #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID href] for the
        #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID a] #[+Term--YDID tag] as once final link has been clicked or tapped,
        the telephony software will be opened and it will be suggested to call to the phone number specified
        via #[+Keyphrase--YDID single] #[+Term--YDID parameter].
      On the #[+Term--YDID smartphones] such software is definitely exists, on other types of devices probably
        it will be suggested to select the telephony software such as #[+SecondaryEntity--YDID Skype],
        #[+SecondaryEntity--YDID People], etc., however most likely it will require to pay for the calling
        to the phone number.

    +CodeViewer--YDF
      +CodeViewer-Listing--YDF({ codeLanguage: CodeViewer__YDF.SupportedCodesLanguages.Pug }).
        a(
          href=buildPhoneNumberLinkHrefAttributeValue("+447975777666")
        ) 79757-77666

    p.Article-Paragraph.
      All that this #[+Term--YDID function] doing is appending the #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID tel:] to the
        specified #[+Term--YDID string value] which expected to be the valid phone number.
      If your text editor of the #[+Term--YDID Integrated Development Environment] (#[+Term--YDID IDE]) have
        #[+Keyword--YDID no] the functionality of the autocompleting according the templates, this #[+Term--YDID function]
        hardly will be useful for you: #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID tel:] or
        the #[+Term--YDID function] name #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID buildPhoneNumberLinkHrefAttributeValue], you will
        need either to memorize it or check the reference guide every time (although there is just three alphabetic
        letters in #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID tel:], together with large volume of the other information even
        it could be forgot).

    p.Article-Paragraph
      | If the autocompletion by the templates functionality is presents, it is enough to begin to input
      |   #[+SecondaryEntity__Code--YDID buildP...], then the popup hint will appear and the further actions depends
      |   on how the autocomplete has been implemented in the text editor or #[+Term--YDID IDE].
      | In the case of the
